main event: Two objects were observed moving in different patterns in the northern sky over Athens, Ohio on October 14, 1966.
interesting points: The objects would vary in brightness, becoming very dim and only visible with the use of binoculars before fading out.
The objects executed 'violent flashes' at their turn points, and the color changed when they flashed compared to their regular path.
At one point, both objects were visible in the binoculars at the same time, crossing paths.
The observer could not definitively determine the speed and distance of the objects, though initial estimates were provided.
In addition to the two main objects, the observer reported seeing other aircraft and a satellite in the sky during the sighting.
